  src="https://mapgenie.io/zelda-breath-of-the-wild/maps/hyrule?embed=light" 
  height="500" 
  style="position: relative; width: 100%;">
</iframe>

<h2>Main Quest Progression</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Main Quest</th>
    <th>Region</th>
    <th>Objectives</th>
    <th>Tips</th>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>The Great Plateau</td>
    <td>Great Plateau</td>
    <td>Activate the Sheikah Tower, complete the four trial shrines, obtain the Paraglider.</td>
    <td>Use bombs to conserve weapon durability; climb early to get a sense of the terrain.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Seek Out Impa</td>
    <td>Kakariko Village</td>
    <td>Travel east through Dueling Peaks to meet Impa and unlock the main storyline.</td>
    <td>Stop at the Dueling Peaks Stable for inventory upgrades and side quests.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Free the Divine Beasts</td>
    <td>Various Regions</td>
    <td>Complete the four Champion arcs in Zora, Goron, Rito, and Gerudo lands.</td>
    <td>Approach in any order; consider starting with Vah Ruta for the easiest boss fight.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Destroy Ganon</td>
    <td>Hyrule Castle</td>
    <td>Storm the castle and defeat Calamity Ganon.</td>
    <td>Use Revali’s Gale to access higher floors quickly; stock up on ancient arrows.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>Shrines Overview</h2>
<p>
Each of the 120 shrines offers puzzles, combat trials, or blessings that reward Spirit Orbs.  
Collect four orbs to upgrade either your hearts or stamina, allowing deeper exploration and more challenging battles.
</p>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Shrine Name</th>
    <th>Region</th>
    <th>Type</th>
    <th>Key Insight</th>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Oman Au Shrine</td>
    <td>Great Plateau</td>
    <td>Magnesis Trial</td>
    <td>Master magnet manipulation to solve puzzles involving metal blocks.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Ja Baij Shrine</td>
    <td>Great Plateau</td>
    <td>Bomb Trial</td>
    <td>Learn remote bomb usage for combat and environmental puzzles.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Owa Daim Shrine</td>
    <td>Great Plateau</td>
    <td>Stasis Trial</td>
    <td>Stop moving objects to create momentum; use this technique later in many puzzles.</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>Ke Numut Shrine</td>
    <td>Great Plateau</td>
    <td>Cryonis Trial</td>
    <td>Create ice pillars to climb, block water attacks, and navigate watery terrain.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>Side Quests & Exploration</h2>
<p>
Breath of the Wild’s vast open world is packed with over 70 side quests, 76 sub-quests,  
and countless hidden secrets. Completing these quests rewards players with useful items,  
armor pieces, rupees, and unique weapons. Explore every stable, village, and mountain peak—
Hyrule rewards curiosity.
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Tarrey Town Questline:</strong> Build a full town and unlock special vendors.</li>
  <li><strong>EX DLC Quests:</strong> Find hidden armor sets like Majora’s Mask and the Phantom armor.</li>
  <li><strong>Horse Upgrades:</strong> Discover the Malanya Spring to enhance your horses.</li>
  <li><strong>Dragon Encounters:</strong> Harvest scales, claws, and fangs for high-level upgrades.</li>
</ul>

<p>
Use this guide as your companion through Hyrule—whether you’re hunting shrines,  
mastering shield surfing, cooking powerful meals, or taking down Ganon,  
you’ll have everything you need for a full 100% completion journey.
</p>
